column1:
goto <setting>[.<prop>] | <prop>  :: enter setting/property for editing

This command enters into a setting or property for editing it.

Examples: nmcli> goto connection
          nmcli connection> goto secondaries
          nmcli> goto ipv4.addresses
column3:
goto <roghainn>[.<buadh>] | <buadh>     :: rach a-steach dha roghainn/buadh
                                           a chum deasachaidh

Bheir an àithne seo gu roghainn no buadh thu ach an deasaich thu i.

Mar eisimpleir: nmcli> goto connection
                nmcli connection> goto secondaries
                nmcli> goto ipv4.addresses

column1:
remove <setting>[.<prop>]  :: remove setting or reset property value

This command removes an entire setting from the connection, or if a property
is given, resets that property to the default value.

Examples: nmcli> remove wifi-sec
          nmcli> remove eth.mtu
column3:
remove <roghainn>[.<buadh>]             :: thoir roghainn air falbh no
                                           ath-shuidhich luach buaidhe

Bheir an àitne seo air falbh roghainn shlàn on cheangal, no ma chaidh buadh a thoirt
seachad, ath-shuidhichidh e a' bhuadh sin air an luach tùsail.

Mar eisimpleir: nmcli> remove wifi-sec
                nmcli> remove eth.mtu

column1:
set [<setting>.<prop> <value>]  :: set property value

This command sets property value.

Example: nmcli> set con.id My connection
column3:
set [<roghainn>.<buadh> <luach>]        :: suidhich luach na buaidh

Suidhichidh an àithne seo luach buaidh.

Mar eisimpleir: nmcli> set con.id An ceangal agam

column1:
describe [<setting>.<prop>]  :: describe property

Shows property description. You can consult nm-settings(5) manual page to see all NM settings and properties.
column3:
describe [<roghainn>.<buadh>]  :: mìnich a' bhuadh

Seall tuairisgeul na buaidh. Thoir sùil air duilleag an leabhair-mìneachaidh aig
nm-settings(5) gus a h-uile roghainn is buadh aig NM a shealltainn.

column1:
print [all]  :: print setting or connection values

Shows current property or the whole connection.

Example: nmcli ipv4> print all
column3:
print [all]  :: seall fiosrachadh roghainn no luachan a' cheangail

Seallaidh seo a' bhuadh làithreach no an ceangal air fad.

Mar eisimpleir: nmcli ipv4> print all

column1:
---[ Property menu ]---
set      [<value>]               :: set new value
add      [<value>]               :: add new option to the property
change                           :: change current value
remove   [<index> | <option>]    :: delete the value
describe                         :: describe property
print    [setting | connection]  :: print property (setting/connection) value(s)
back                             :: go to upper level
help/?   [<command>]             :: print this help or command description
quit                             :: exit nmcli
column3:
---[ Clàr-taice na buaidh ]---
set      [<luach>]                :: suidhich luach ùr
add      [<luach>]                :: cuir an roghainn ùr ris a' bhuadh
change                            :: atharraich an luach làithreach
remove   [<inneacs> | <roghainn>] :: sguab às an luach
describe                          :: mìnich a' bhuadh
print    [setting | connection]   :: seall luach(an) na buaidh (roghainn/ceangal)
back                              :: rach gu leibheil nas àirde
help/?   [<àithne>]               :: seall a' chobhair seo no tuairisgeul na h-àithne
quit                              :: fàg nmcli

column1:
set [<value>]  :: set new value

This command sets provided <value> to this property
column3:
set [<luach>]  :: suidhich luach ùr

Suidhichidh an àithne seo a' bhuadh seo air an <luach> a chaidh a shònrachadh

column1:
add [<value>]  :: append new value to the property

This command adds provided <value> to this property, if the property is of a container type. For single-valued properties the property value is replaced (same as 'set').
column3:
add [<luach>]  :: cuir luach ùr ris a' bhuadh

Cuiridh an àithne seo an <luach> a chaidh a shònrachadh ris a' bhuadh seo ma tha
a' bhuadh 'na soitheach. Airson buadhan le luach a-mhàin, thèid luach na buaidh
a chur an àite (mar a nì "set").

column1:
describe  :: describe property

Shows property description. You can consult nm-settings(5) manual page to see all NM settings and properties.
column3:
describe  :: mìnich a' bhuadh

Seall tuairisgeul na buaidh. Thoir sùil air duilleag an leabhair-mìneachaidh aig
nm-settings(5) gus a h-uile roghainn is buadh aig NM a shealltainn.

column1:
print [property|setting|connection]  :: print property (setting, connection) value(s)

Shows property value. Providing an argument you can also display values for the whole setting or connection.
column3:
print [buadh|roghainn|ceangal]  :: seall luach(an) buaidh (roghainn, ceangal)

Seallaidh seo luach na buaidh. Ma bheir thu seachad argamaid, 's urrainn dhut luachan
a shealltainn airson na roghainn no a' cheangail gu lèir cuideachd.
Luachan a tha ceadaichte airson na buaidh \"%s\": %s\n
Mearachd: cha deach leinn a' bhuadh \"%s\" a shuidheachadh: %s\n
Mearachd: tha roghainn a dhìth air a' bhuadh \"%s\"\n

column1: A simple application to keep your disk usage and available space under control.

column1: Disk Usage Analyzer can scan specific folders, storage devices and online accounts. It provides both a tree and a graphical representation showing the size of each folder, making it easy to identify where disk space is wasted.
column3: ’S urrainn dha Sgrùdair cleachdadh nan diosga pasganan sònraichte, uidheaman stòrais agus cunntasan air loidhne a sganadh. Bheir e an dà chuid sealladh craoibhe is riochdachadh grafaigeach dhut a sheallas meud gach pasgain ach am faic thu gun duilgheadas càit a bheil àite ’ga chaitheamh air an diosga.

column1: The Eye of GNOME is the official image viewer for the GNOME desktop. It integrates with the GTK+ look and feel of GNOME, and supports many image formats for viewing single images or images in a collection.
column3: ’S e an sealladair-dhealbhan oifigeil aig an deasg GNOME a th’ annn an Eye of GNOME. Amalaichidh e le gnàth GTK+ aig GNOME agus cuiridh e taic ri iomadh fòrmat deilbh gus dealbhan fa leth no cruinneachaidhean dhiubh a shealltainn.

column1: The Eye of GNOME also allows to view the images in a fullscreen slideshow mode or set an image as the desktop wallpaper. It reads the camera tags to automatically rotate your images in the correct portrait or landscape orientation.
column3: Leigidh Eye of GNOME leat cuideachd na dealbhan a shealltainn ann am modh taisbeanadh-dhealbhan làn-sgrìn no dealbh a chleachdadh mar chùlaibh an deasga. Leughaidh e tagaichean camara gus na dealbhan agad a chuairteachadh ’nam portraid no cruth-tìre gu fèin-obrachail ’s mar bu chòir.
Rèidhich na dealbhan nuair a bhios iad air an sùmadh a-_mach
Rèidhich na dealbhan nuair a bhios iad air an sùmadh a-_steach

column1: Whether the image should be rotated automatically based on EXIF orientation.
column3: Co-dhiù an tèid an dealbh a chuairteachadh gu fèin-obrachail, stèidhichte air a’ chomhair EXIF.

column1: The color that is used to fill the area behind the image. If the use-background-color key is not set, the color is determined by the active GTK+ theme instead.
column3: An dath a thèid a chleachdadh gus an raon air cùlaibh an deilbh a lìonadh. Mur deach an iuchair use-background-color a shuidheachadh, bidh an dath a-rèir an ùrlair GTK+ ghnìomhaich.

column1: Whether the image should be interpolated on zoom-out. This leads to better quality but is somewhat slower than non-interpolated images.
column3: Co-dhiù an tèid an dealbh eadar-phòlachadh nuair a thèid a sùmadh a-mach. Bidh càileachd nas fhearr air an dealbh ach bheir seo beagan ùine a bharrachd.

column1: Whether the image should be extrapolated on zoom-in. This leads to blurry quality and is somewhat slower than non-extrapolated images.
column3: Co-dhiù an tèid an dealbh às-phòlachadh nuair a thèid a sùmadh a-steach. Cuiridh seo beagan sgleò air an dealbh is bheir seo beagan ùine a bharrachd.

column1: Determines how transparency should be indicated. Valid values are CHECK_PATTERN, COLOR and NONE. If COLOR is chosen, then the trans-color key determines the color value used.
column3: Suidhichidh seo mar a thèid trìd-shoillearachd a thaisbeanadh. Is CHECK_PATTERN, COLOR is NONE na luachan dligheach. Ma thaghas tu COLOR, bidh luach an datha a-rèir na h-iuchrach trans-color.

column1: Whether the scroll wheel should be used for zooming.
column3: Co-dhiù an tèid an cuibhle sgrolaidh a chleachdadh airson sùmadh.

column1: The multiplier to be applied when using the mouse scroll wheel for zooming. This value defines the zooming step used for each scroll event. For example, 0.05 results in a 5% zoom increment for each scroll event and 1.00 result in a 100% zoom increment.
column3: Seo an t-iomadair a thèid a chur an sàs nuair a thèid sùmadh leis a’ chuibhle sùmaidh. Suidhichidh an luach seo ceum an t-sùmaidh airson gach tachartas sgrolaidh. Mar eisimpleir, bheir 0.05 meudachadh sùmaidh de 5% dhut leis gach tachartas sgrolaidh is bheir 1.00 meudachadh sùmaidh de 100% dhut.

column1: If the transparency key has the value COLOR, then this key determines the color which is used for indicating transparency.
column3: Mas e COLOR a tha san iuchair transparency, suidhichidh an iuchair seo an dath a thaisbeanas an trìd-shoilleireachd.

column1: If this is active, the color set by the background-color key will be used to fill the area behind the image. If it is not set, the current GTK+ theme will determine the fill color.
column3: Ma tha seo gnìomhach, thèid an dath aig an iuchair background-color a chleachdadh gus an raon air cùlaibh an deilbh a lìonadh. Mur eil seo suidhichte bidh dath an lìonaidh a-rèir an ùrlair GTK+ làithrich.

column1: Whether the sequence of images should be shown in an endless loop.
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid an sreath dhealbhan a shealltainn ann an lùb gun chrìch.
Ceadaich sùm nas motha na 100% aig an toiseach

column1: If this is set to FALSE small images will not be stretched to fit into the screen initially.
column3: Mas e FALSE a th’ ann, cha tèid dealbhan beaga a mheudachadh ach an co-fhreagair iad ris an sgrìn aig an toiseach.

column1: Delay in seconds until showing the next image
column3: Dàil ann an diogan gus an tèid an ath dhealbh a shealltainn

column1: A value greater than 0 determines the seconds an image stays on screen until the next one is shown automatically. Zero disables the automatic browsing.
column3: Suidhichidh luach nas motha na 0 na diogan a mhaireas dealbh air an sgrìn mus tèid an ath fhear a shealltainn gu fèin-obrachail. Cuiridh neoni am brabhsadh fèin-obrachail à comas.

column1: Image gallery pane position. Set to 0 for bottom; 1 for left; 2 for top; 3 for right.
column3: An t-ionad aig leòsan a’ ghailearaidh dhealbhan. Suidhich air 0 airson a’ bhuinn; 1 airson an taoibh chlì; 2 airson a’ bharra; 3 airson an taoibh dheas.

column1: Whether the image gallery pane should be resizable.
column3: Co-dhiù an gabh leòsan a’ ghailearaidh dhealbhan ath-mheudachadh.

column1: Show/Hide the image gallery pane scroll buttons.
column3: Seall/Falaich na putanan sgrolaidh aig leòsan a’ ghailearaidh dhealbhan

column3: Dùin a’ phrìomh uinneag gun fhaighneachd a bheilear airson na h-atharraichean a shàbhaladh.
Cuir dealbhan dhan sgudal gun dearbhadh

column1: If activated, Eye of GNOME won’t ask for confirmation when moving images to the trash. It will still ask if any of the files cannot be moved to the trash and would be deleted instead.
column3: Ma tha seo gnìomhach, chan fhaighnich Eye of GNOME airson dearbhadh nuair a thèid dealbhan a chur dhan sgudal. Faighnichidh e fhathast mur gabh gin dhe na faidhlichean a ghluasad dhan sgudal is nan rachadh sguabadh às dhaibh na àite.

column1: Whether the file chooser should show the user’s pictures folder if no images are loaded.
column3: Co-dhiù an seall roghnaichear nam faidhle am pasgan dhealbhan aig a’ chleachdaiche mur deach dealbh a luchdadh.

column1: If activated and no image is loaded in the active window, the file chooser will display the user’s pictures folder using the XDG special user directories. If deactivated or the pictures folder has not been set up, it will show the current working directory.
column3: Ma tha seo gnìomhach gun dealbh air a luchdadh san uinneag ghnìomhach, seallaidh roghnaichear nam faidhle am pasgan dhealbhan aig a’ chleachdaiche, a’ chleachdadh pasganan sònraichte XDG a’ chleachdaiche. Ma tha seo à gnìomh no mur deach pasgan dhealbhan a shuidheachadh, seallaidh e am pasgan obrach làithreach.

column1: Whether the metadata list in the properties dialog should have its own page.
column3: Co-dhiù am bi duilleag fa leth aig liosta a’ mheata-dàta ann an còmhradh nan roghainnean.

column1: If activated, the detailed metadata list in the properties dialog will be moved to its own page in the dialog. This should make the dialog more usable on smaller screens, e.g. as used by netbooks. If disabled, the widget will be embedded on the “Metadata” page.
column3: Ma tha seo gnìomhach, thèid liosta mionaideach a’ mheata-dàta ann an còmhradh nan roghainnean a ghluasad gu duilleag aige fhèin sa chòmhradh. Bidh an còmhradh nas fhasa cleachdadh air sgrìnichean beaga le sin, mar eisimpleir air netbook. Ma tha seo à comas, thèid am widget a leabachadh air an duilleag “Meata-dàta”.

column1: List of active plugins. It doesn’t contain the “Location” of the active plugins. See the .eog-plugin file for obtaining the “Location” of a given plugin.

column1:
Scale document pages to fit the selected printer page. Select from one of the following:

• “None”: No page scaling is performed.

• “Shrink to Printable Area”: Document pages larger than the printable area are reduced to fit the printable area of the printer page.

• “Fit to Printable Area”: Document pages are enlarged or reduced as required to fit the printable area of the printer page.
column3:
Sgèilich duilleagan na sgrìobhainn ach an co-fhreagair iad ri duilleag a’ chlò-bhualadair. Tagh aon dhe na roghainnean seo:

• “Chan eil gin”: Cha tèid duilleag a sgèileachadh.

• “Lùghdaich gun raon a ghabhas clò-bhualadh”: Thèid duilleagan san sgrìobhainn a tha nas motha na an raon a ghabhas clò-bhualadh a lùghdachadh ach an co-fhreagair iad ris an raon a ghabhas clò-bhualadh air duilleag a’ chlò-bhualadair.

• “Co-fhreagair ris an raon a ghabhas clò-bhualadh”: Thèid duilleagan na sgrìobhainn a mheudachadh no a lùghdachadh ach an co-fhreagair iad ris an raon a ghabhas clò-bhualadh air duilleag a’ chlò-bhualadair.

column1: This is a document viewer for the GNOME desktop.
column3: Seo sealladair sgrìobhainnean airson an deasg GNOME.

column1: It supports the following document formats: PDF, PS, EPS, XPS, DjVu, TIFF, DVI (with SyncTeX), and Comic Books archives (CBR, CBT, CBZ, CB7).
column3: Cuiridh e taic dha na fòrmatan seo: PDF, PS, EPS, XPS, DjVu, TIFF, DVI (le SyncTeX) agus tasglannan Comic Books (CBR, CBT, CBZ, CB7).

column1: Open, modify and create compressed archive files
column3: Fosgail, atharraich is cruthaich tasglannan dùmhlaichte de dh’fhaidhlichean

column1: Archive Manager (also known as File Roller) is the default GNOME application for opening, creating, and modifying archive and compressed archive files.
column3: ’S e an aplacaid GNOME thùsail gus faidhlichean tasglainn ’s faidhlichean tasglainn dùmhlaichte fhosgladh, a chruthachadh ’s a dheasachadh a th’ ann am Manaidsear nan tasglann (air a bheil File Roller cuideachd).

column1: Archive Manager supports a wide range of different archive files, including:
column3: Cuiridh Manaidsear nan tasglannan taic ri roghainn fharsaing de dh’fhaidhlichean tasglainn, a’ gabhail a-steach:

column1: What criteria must be used to arrange files. Possible values: name, size, type, time, path.
column3: Na cuspairean-deuchainn a thèid a chleachdadh gus faidhlichean a sheòrsachadh. Seo na luachan a dh’fhaodadh a bhith ann: name, size, type, time, path.

column1: Whether to sort in ascending or descending direction. Possible values: ascending, descending.

column1: Take a picture of the screen
gedit is the official text editor of the GNOME desktop environment. While aiming at simplicity and ease of use, gedit is a powerful general purpose text editor.
column3: ’S e an deasaiche teacsa oifigeil airson àrainneachd deasga GNOME a th’ anns an gedit. ’S e deasaiche teacsa coitcheann cumhachdach a th’ ann an gedit ged a tha e ag amas a bhith simplidh agus furasta cleachdadh.

column1: Whether you are writing the next bestseller, programming an innovative application, or simply taking some quick notes, gedit will be a reliable tool to accomplish your task.
column3: Co-dhiù a bheil thu airson nobhail no prògram no gearr-nòtaichean a sgrìobhadh, ’s e acainn sheasmhach a bhios ann an gedit gus na tha fainear dhut a thoirt gu buil.

column1: Its flexible plugin system allows you to tailor the application to your needs and adapt it to your workflow.
column3: Leigidh an siostam plugain sùbailte aige leat gun gnàthaich thu an aplacaid a-rèir nam feumalachdan ’s an dòigh-obrach agad.

column1: Whether to use the system’s default fixed width font for editing text instead of a font specific to gedit. If this option is turned off, then the font named in the “Editor Font” option will be used instead of the system font.
column3: An dèid cruth-clò bunaiteach an t-siostaim le leud socraichte a chleachdadh gus teacsa a dheasachadh seach an cruth-clò sònraichte aig gedit. Ma tha an roghainn seo dheth, thèid an cruth-clò ainmichte san roghainn “Cruth-clò an deasaiche” a chleachdadh an àite cruth-clò an t-siostaim.

column1: A custom font that will be used for the editing area. This will only take effect if the “Use Default Font” option is turned off.
column3: Cruth-clò gnàthaichte a thèid a chleachdadh airson an raon deasachaidh. Cha dèid seo a chur an sàs ach ma bhios an roghainn “Cleachd an cruth-clò bunaiteach” air a chur dheth.

column1: The ID of a GtkSourceView Style Scheme used to color the text.
column3: An ID aig sgeama stoidhle GtkSourceView a thèid a chleachdadh gus dath a chur air an teacsa.

column1: Whether gedit should create backup copies for the files it saves.
column3: Co-dhiù an cruthaich gedit lethbhreac-glèidhidh dhe na faidhlichean a shàbhaileas e gus nach cruthaich.

column1: Whether gedit should automatically save modified files after a time interval. You can set the time interval with the “Autosave Interval” option.
column3: An sàbhail gedit faidhlichean air an atharrachadh gu fèin-obrachail an ceann ùine. ’S urrainn dhut suidheachadh dè cho tric ’s a thèid seo a dhèanamh leis an roghainn “Earadamh an t-sàbhalaidh fhèin-obrachail”.

column1: Number of minutes after which gedit will automatically save modified files. This will only take effect if the “Autosave” option is turned on.
column3: An ceann co mheud mionaid a thòisicheas gedit le sàbhaladh fèin-obrachail nam faidhlichean air an atharrachadh. Chan eil an roghainn seo an sàs ach nuair a bhios “Sàbhaladh fèin-obrachail” air a chur air.
An àireamh as motha de ghnìomhan neo-dhèanaimh

column1: Maximum number of actions that gedit will be able to undo or redo. Use “-1” for unlimited number of actions.
column3: An àireamh as motha de ghnìomhan as urrainn dha gedit a neo-dhèanamh no ath-dhèanamh. Cleachd “-1” airson an gnìomhan gun chuingeachadh.

column1: Specifies how to wrap long lines in the editing area. Use “none” for no wrapping, “word” for wrapping at word boundaries, and “char” for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: Sònraichidh seo mar a thèid loidhnichean fada a phasgadh san raon deasachaidh. Cleachd “neoni” mur eil thu airson pasgadh sam bith, “word” airson pasgadh eadar dà fhacal is “char” airson pasgadh eadar dà charactar sam bith. Thoir an aire gun toir na luachan an aire do litrichean mòra is beaga ’s mar sin dèan cinnteach gu nochd iad dìreach mar a thug sinn iomradh orra an-seo.

column1: Last split mode choice for line wrapping mode
column3: Am modh sgoltaidh airson pasgadh loidhne mu dheireadh a chaidh a thaghadh

column1: Specifies the last split mode used with line wrapping mode, so that when wrapping mode is off we still remember the split mode choice. Use “word” for wrapping at word boundaries, and “char” for wrapping at individual character boundaries.
column3: Sònraichidh seo am modh sgoltaidh a chaidh a chleachdadh leis a’ mhodh pasgaidh loidhne an turas mu dheireadh ach an cuimhnich sinn na thagh thu fiù ’s ma tha am modh pasgaidh loidhne dheth. Cleachd “word” airson pasgadh aig crìochan facail agus “char” gus sgoltadh eadar caractaran.

column1: Specifies the number of spaces that should be displayed instead of Tab characters.
column3: Sònraichidh seo an àireamh de spàsan a thèid a shealltainn an àite caractar taba.

column1: Whether gedit should insert spaces instead of tabs.
column3: Co-dhiù an cuir gedit spàsan a-steach an àite thabaichean gus nach cuir.

column1: Whether gedit should enable automatic indentation.
column3: Co-dhiù an cleachd gedit eagan fèin-obrachail gus nach cleachd.

column1: Whether gedit should display line numbers in the editing area.
column3: Co-dhiù an seall gedit àireamhan loidhne san raon deasachaidh gus nach seall.

column1: Whether gedit should highlight the current line.
column3: Co-dhiù an soillsich gedit an loidhne làithreadh gus nach soillsich.

column1: Whether gedit should highlight matching brackets.
column3: Co-dhiù an soillsich gedit camagan a cho-fhreagras gus nach soillsich.

column1: Whether gedit should display the right margin in the editing area.
column3: Co-dhiù an seall gedit am marghan deas gus nach seall.

column1: Specifies the position of the right margin.
column3: Sònraichidh seo ionad a’ mharghain dheis.

column1: Whether gedit should display the overview map for the document.
column3: Co-dhiù an seall gedit mapa foir-sheallaidh deas gus nach seall.
Seòrsa a’ phàtrain air cùlaibh na sgrìobhainn

column1: Whether the document will get a background pattern painted.
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid pàtran a pheantadh air cùlaibh na sgrìobhainn gus nach dèid.

column1: Specifies how the cursor moves when the HOME and END keys are pressed. Use “disabled” to always move at the start/end of the line, “after” to move to the start/end of the line the first time the keys are pressed and to the start/end of the text ignoring whitespaces the second time the keys are pressed, “before” to move to the start/end of the text before moving to the start/end of the line and “always” to always move to the start/end of the text instead of the start/end of the line.
column3: Sònraichidh seo mar a ghluaiseas an cùrsair nuair a thèid an iuchair HOME agus END a bhrùthadh. Cleachd “disabled” airson ’s gun gluais e gu toiseach/deireadh na loidhne, “after” airson ’s gun gluais e gu toiseach/deireadh na loidhne a’ chiad turas a bhrùthar an dà iuchair còmhla agus gu toiseach/deireadh an teacsa (a’ leigeil seachad àitichean bàna) an dàrna turas a bhrùthar iad, “before” gus gluasad gu toiseach/deireadh an teacsa mus gluais e gu toiseach/deireadh na loidhne agus “always” airson ’s gun gluais e gu toiseach/deireadh an teacsa seach toiseach/deireadh na loidhne.

column1: Whether gedit should restore the previous cursor position when a file is loaded.
column3: Co-dhiù an aisig gedit àite a’ chùrsair roimhe nuair a thèid faidhle a luchdadh gus nach aisig.
Cuir an comas soillseachadh a’ cho-chàraidh

column1: Whether gedit should enable syntax highlighting.
column3: Co-dhiù an cuir gedit soillseachadh a’ cho-chàraidh an comas gus nach cuir.
Cuir an comas soillseachadh an luirg

column1: Whether gedit should highlight all the occurrences of the searched text.
column3: Co-dhiù an soillsich gedit gach ball-toraidh dhen teacsa a lorg thu gus nach soillsich.
Dèan cinnteach gum bi loidhne ùr aig bonn an teacsa

column1: Whether gedit will ensure that documents always end with a trailing newline.
column3: Tagh an dèan gedit cinnteach gum bidh loidhne ùr aig deireadh gach teacsa.

column1: Whether the toolbar should be visible in editing windows.
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid am bàr-inneal a shealltainn gus nach dèid.

column1: Specifies when to show the notebook tabs. Use “never” to never show the tabs, “always” to always show the tabs, and “auto” to show the tabs only when there is more than one tab. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: Sònraichidh seo cuin a thèid tabaichean an leabhair-nòtaichean a shealltainn. Cleachd “never” ach nach dèid na tabaichean a shealltainn idir, “always” ach an dèid iad a shealltainn an-còmhnaidh is “auto” gus nach dèid na tabaichean a shealltainn ach nuair a bhios barrachd air aon dhiubh ann. Thoir an aire gun toir na luachan an aire do litrichean mòra is beaga is mar sin dèan cinnteach gun nochd iad dìreach mar a tha sinn a’ toirt iomradh dhaibh an-seo.

column1: Whether the status bar at the bottom of editing windows should be visible.
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid am bàr-staide a shealltainn aig bonn nan uinneagan deasachaidh gus nach dèid.

column1: Whether the side panel at the left of editing windows should be visible.
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid a’ phanail taobh clì nan uinneagan deasachaidh a shealltainn gus nach dèid.
An àireamh as motha de dh’fhaidhlichean o chionn ghoirid

column1: Specifies the maximum number of recently opened files that will be displayed in the “Recent Files” submenu.
column3: Sònraichidh seo an àireamh nas motha de dh’fhaidhlichean air am fosgladh o chionn ghoirid a thèid a shealltainn sa fho-chlàr-taice “Faidhlichean o chionn ghoirid”.

column1: Whether gedit should print syntax highlighting when printing documents.
column3: Tagh an clò-bhuail gedit soillseachadh a’ cho-chàraidh nuair a thèid sgrìobhainn a chlò-bhualadh.

column1: Whether gedit should include a document header when printing documents.
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid bann-cinn sgrìobhainne a ghabhail a-steach gus nach dèid nuair a thèid sgrìobhainn a chlò-bhualadh.

column1: Specifies how to wrap long lines for printing. Use “none” for no wrapping, “word” for wrapping at word boundaries, and “char” for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: Sònraichidh seo ciamar a thèid loidhnichean fada a phasgadh airson clò-bhualadh. Cleachd “none” ach nach bith pasgadh sam bith ann, “word” airson pasgadh eadar da fhacal is “char” airson pasgadh eadar dà charactar sam bith. Thoir an aire gun toir na luachan aire do litrichean mòra is beaga is mar sin dèan cinnteach gun nochd iad dìreach mar a tha sinn a’ toirt iomradh dhaibh an-seo.

column1: If this value is 0, then no line numbers will be inserted when printing a document. Otherwise, gedit will print line numbers every such number of lines.
column3: Mas e 0 a tha san luach seo, cha dèid àireamh loidhne sam bith a chur a-steach nuair a chlò-bhuaileas tu sgrìobhainn. Mas e luach eile a tha ann, mìnichidh e dè cho tric ’s a chlò-bhuaileas gedit àireamh loidhne. Mar eisimpleir, thèid àireamh a chlò-bhualadh gach treas loidhne ma chuireas tu 3 a-steach.

column1: Specifies the font to use for a document’s body when printing documents.
column3: Sònraichidh seo an cruth-clò a thèid a chleachdadh airson bodhaig an teacsa nuair a thèid sgrìobhainn a chlò-bhualadh.

column1: Specifies the font to use for page headers when printing a document. This will only take effect if the “Print Header” option is turned on.
column3: Sònraichidh seo an cruth-clò a thèid a chleachdadh airson bannan-cinn na duilleige nuair a thèid sgrìobhainn a chlò-bhualadh. Cha bhith seo an sàs ach ma bhios an roghainn “Clò-bhuail bann-cinn” air.
Cruth-clò na h-àireamh loidhne airson clò-bhualadh

column1: Specifies the font to use for line numbers when printing. This will only take effect if the “Print Line Numbers” option is non-zero.
column3: Sònraichidh seo an cruth-clò a thèid a chleachdadh airson àireamhan loidhne leis a’ chlò-bhualadh. Cha bhi seo an sàs ach ma bhios an roghainn “Clò-bhuail àireamhan loidhne” nas motha na neoni.
Am marghan clì ann am millemeatair.
Am marghan aig a’ bharr ann am millemeatair.
Am marghan deas ann am millemeatair.
Am marghan aig a’ bhonn ann am millemeatair.

column1: List of candidate encodings shown in the Character Encoding menu in the open/save file chooser. “CURRENT” represents the current locale encoding. Only recognized encodings are used. The default value is the empty list, in which case gedit will choose good defaults depending on the country and language.
column3: Liosta dhe na còdachaidhean a thèid a mholadh dhut ann an clàr-taice còdachadh charactaran fhad ’s a bhios tu a’ taghadh faidhle airson fosgladh/sàbhaladh. Tha “CURRENT” a’ riochdachadh còdachadh an sgeama ionadail làithrich. Cha dèid ach còdachaidhean as aithne dhuinn a chleachdadh. ’S e an liosta fhalamh a tha sa bhun-roghainn leis a thaghas gedit bun-roghainnean matha a-rèir do dhùthaich is cànan.

column1: List of active plugins. It contains the “Location” of the active plugins. See the .gedit-plugin file for obtaining the “Location” of a given plugin.
column3: Liosta dhe na plugain ghnìomhach. Tha “ionad” nam plugan gnìomhach na bhroinn. Thoir sùil air an fhaidhle .gedit-plugin airson an t-ionad aig plugain sònraichte fhaighinn.

column1: Display list of possible values for the encoding option
column3: Seall liosta dhe na luachan comasach airson na roghainn còdachaidh

column1: Set the character encoding to be used to open the files listed on the command line
column3: Suidhich an còdachadh charactaran a thèid a chleachdadh gus na faidhlichean fhosgladh ’s liosta dhiubh air an loidhne-àithne

column1: Create a new top-level window in an existing instance of gedit
column3: Cruthaich uinneag àrd-ìre ùr ann an ionstans de gedit a tha ann

column1: Create a new document in an existing instance of gedit
column3: Cruthaich sgrìobhainn ùr ann an ionstans de gedit a tha ann

column1: Open files and block process until files are closed
column3: Fosgail faidhlichean is bac am pròiseas gus am bi na faidhlichean air an dùnadh

column1: Calculates the number of compounding periods necessary to increase an investment of present value to a future value, at a fixed interest rate per compounding period.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an àireamh de dh’fhaidean-ùine fillte air a bhios feum gus inbheisteadh a mheudachadh on luach làithreach gu luach ri teachd, le luach-rèidh socraichte rè gach faid-ùine fillte.

column1: Calculates the depreciation allowance on an asset for a specified period of time, using the double-declining balance method.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an dìmeasadh a tha ceadaichte air maoin thar ùine socraichte le modh an dìmeasaidh crìonaidh dhùbailte.

column1: Calculates the future value of an investment based on a series of equal payments at a periodic interest rate over the number of payment periods in the term.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an luach ri teachd aig inbheisteadh, stèidhichte air sreath de phàighidhean co-ionnann le luach-rèidh o àm gu àm thar an uiread de dh’fhaidean-ùine pàighidh san teirm.

column1: Calculates the resale price of a product, based on the product cost and the wanted gross profit margin.
column3: Cunntaidh seo a’ phrìs ath-reic aig bathar, stèidhichte air cosgaisean a’ bhathair agus marghan na prothaid iomlain a tha fainear dhut.

column1: Calculates the amount of the periodic payment of a loan, where payments are made at the end of each payment period.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an luach aig pàigheadh o àm gu àm aig iasad nuair a thèid pàigheadh air deireadh gach faid-ùine pàighidh.

column1: Calculates the present value of an investment based on a series of equal payments discounted at a periodic interest rate over the number of payment periods in the term.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an luach làithreach aig inbheisteadh, stèidhichte air sreath de phàighidhean co-ionnann ìslichte le luach-rèidh o àm gu àm thar an uiread de dh’fhaidean-ùine pàighidh san teirm.
Reat na rèidh o àm gu àm

column1: Calculates the periodic interest necessary to increase an investment to a future value, over the number of compounding periods.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an riadh o àm gu àm air a bhiodh feum thar an uiread de dh’fhaidean-ùine  fillte gus inbheisteadh a mheudachadh gun luach ri teachd.

column1: Calculates the straight-line depreciation of an asset for one period. The straight-line method of depreciation divides the depreciable cost evenly over the useful life of an asset. The useful life is the number of periods, typically years, over which an asset is depreciated.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an dìmeasadh loidhne dìrich aig maoin rè faid-ùine. Roinnidh am modh loidhne dìrich dìmeasadh an cosgais dìmeasaidh gu cunbhalach thar beatha feumail na maoine. ’S e an uiread de dh’fhaidean-ùine thar an tèid maoin a dhìmeasadh a th’ anns a’ bheatha fheumail, bliadhnaichean mar as trice.
Iomlan an dìmeasaidh fhigearan aig a’ bhliadhna

column1: Calculates the depreciation allowance on an asset for a specified period of time, using the Sum-of-the-Years’-Digits method. This method of depreciation accelerates the rate of depreciation, so that more depreciation expense occurs in earlier periods than in later ones. The useful life is the number of periods, typically years, over which an asset is depreciated.
column3: Cunntaidh seo na tha ceadaichte de dhìmeasadh air maoin airson faid-ùine sònraichte le modh iomlan an dìmeasaidh fhigearan aig a’ bhliadhna. Nì am modh dìmeasaidh seo reat an dìmeasaidh nas luaithe ach an tachair barrachd dìmeasaidh air an toiseach na air an deireadh. ’S e an uiread de dh’fhaidean-ùine thar an tèid maoin a dhìmeasadh a th’ anns a’ bheatha fheumail, bliadhnaichean mar as trice.

column1: Calculates the number of payment periods that are necessary during the term of an ordinary annuity, to accumulate a future value, at a periodic interest rate.
column3: Cunntaidh seo an àireamh de dh’fhaidean-ùine pàighidh air a bhiodh feum rè teirm bliadhnachais àbhaistich gus an luach ri teachd a chruinneachadh le luach-rèidh o àm gu àm.

column1: Sum of the Years Digits Depreciation
column3: Iomlan an dìmeasaidh fhigearan aig a’ bhliadhna

column1: Perform arithmetic, scientific or financial calculations
column3: Dèan cunntadh àireamhachd, saidheansail no ionmhais

column1: GNOME Calculator is an application that solves mathematical equations. Though it at first appears to be a simple calculator with only basic arithmetic operations, you can switch into Advanced, Financial, or Programming mode to find a surprising set of capabilities.
column3: ’S e prògram a tha san Àireamhair GNOME a dh’fhuasglas co-aontaran matamataigeach. Ged a tha coltas an àireamhair shìmplidh air aig nach eil ach obrachaidhean àireamhach bunasach, gabhaidh leum a ghearradh gun mhodh adhartach, ionmhais no prògramachaidh le comasan annasach.

column1: The Advanced calculator supports many operations, including: logarithms, factorials, trigonometric and hyperbolic functions, modulus division, complex numbers, random number generation, prime factorization and unit conversions.
column3: Cuiridh an t-àireamhair adhartach taic ri iomadh obrachadh, a’ gabhail a-steach: log-àireamhan, factarailean, foincseanan triantanach ’s os-bhoileach, roinneadh mòidealais, àireamhan iom-fhillte, gintinn àireamh air thuaiream, factarachadh ann am prìomh-àireamhan agus iompachadh aonadan.

column1: Financial mode supports several computations, including periodic interest rate, present and future value, double declining and straight line depreciation, and many others.
column3: Cuiridh am modh ionmhais taic ris caochladh de chunntaidhean, a’ gabhail a-steach luadh-rèidh o àm gu àm, luach làithreach ’s ri teachd, dìmeasadh crìonaidh dhùbailte ’s loidhne dìrich agus mòran a bharrachd.

column1: Programming mode supports conversion between common bases (binary, octal, decimal, and hexadecimal), boolean algebra, one’s and two’s complementation, character to character code conversion, and more.
column3: Cuiridh am modh prògramachaidh taic ri iompachadh eadar bunaitean coitcheann (bìnearaidh, ochdach, deicheach ’s sia-dheicheach), ailseabra Booleach, co-shlànachadh aon ’s dà, iompachadh o charactar gu caractar agus a bharrachd.

GNOME Calendar is a simple and beautiful calendar application designed to perfectly fit the GNOME desktop. By reusing the components which the GNOME desktop is build on, Calendar nicely integrates with the GNOME ecosystem.

On a tha e ag ath-chleachdadh co-phàirtean air a bheil an deasg GNOME stèidhichte, nì Mìosachan amalachadh ann an àrainneachd GNOME gu dòigheil.

column1: Before calibrating the display, it is recommended to configure your display with the following settings to get optimal results.

column1: Configure your display with custom color settings and ensure the RGB channels are set to the same values.

column1: If custom color is not available then use a 6500K color temperature.

column1: For best results, the display should have been powered for at least 15 minutes before starting the calibration.

column1: A higher precision profile provides higher accuracy in color matching but requires more time for reading the color patches.

column1: Contacts keeps and organize your contacts information. You can create, edit, delete and link together pieces of information about your contacts. Contacts aggregates the details from all your sources providing a centralized place for managing your contacts.

Cuiridh Luchd-aithne a h-uile fiosrachadh o na tùsan agad ri chèile gus prìomh ionad a chruthachadh gus an luchd-aithne agad a stiùireadh.

column1: Calibration will produce a profile that you can use to color manage your screen. The longer you spend on calibration, the better the quality of the color profile.
column3: Cruthaichidh an cailbhreachadh pròifil leis an urrainn dhut na dathan air an sgrìn agad a stiùireadh. Mar as fhaide a bheir thu seachad air a chailbhreachadh, ’s ann as fhearr a bhios pròifil nan dathan agad.

column1: Please set the display to a brightness that is typical for you. Color management will be most accurate at this brightness level.

column3: Air neo ’s urrainn dhut ìre soilleireachd o phròifil eile aig an uidheam seo a chleachdadh.

column1: You can use a color profile on different computers, or even create profiles for different lighting conditions.
column3: ’S urrainn dhut pròifil dhathan a chleachdadh air diofar choimpiutairean no fiù pròifilean a chleachdadh airson diofar ìrean de sholas.

column3: Feumaidh an coimpiutair agad a bhith clàraichte aig an àrainn\nmus urrainn dhut clàradh a-steach Enterprise a dhèanamh. Iarr air\nrianaire an lìonraidh facal-faire na h-àrainne a chur a-steach an-seo.

column1: Authentication is required to change user data
column3: Feumaidh tu dearbhadh a dhèanamh mus urrainn dhut dàta a’ chleachdaiche atharrachadh

column1: The new password needs to be different from the old one.
column3: Chan fhaod an seann fhacal-faire ’s am fear ùr a bhith co-ionnann.

column1: Try changing some letters and numbers.
column3: Feuch is atharraich cuid dhe na litrichean is àireamhan.

column1: Try changing the password a bit more.
column3: Feuch is atharraich am facal-faire beagan a bharrachd

column1: A password without your user name would be stronger.
column3: Bhiodh facal-faire as aonais an ainm-chleachdaiche agad nas làidire.

column1: Try to avoid using your name in the password.
column3: Feuch is na cleachd d’ ainm san fhacal-fhaire.

column1: Try to avoid some of the words included in the password.
column3: Feuch is seachain cuid dhe na faclan a tha san fhacal-fhaire.

column1: Try to avoid reordering existing words.
Try to use more uppercase letters.
column3: Feuch is cleachd barrachd litrichean mòra.

column1: Try to use more lowercase letters.
column3: Feuch is cleachd barrachd litrichean beaga.

column1: Try to use more special characters, like punctuation.
column3: Feuch is cleachd barrachd charactaran sònraichte mar phuingeachadh.

column1: Try to use a mixture of letters, numbers and punctuation.
column3: Feuch is cleachd measgachadh de litrichean, àireamhan is puingeachadh.

column1: Try to avoid repeating the same character.
column3: Feuch is seachain an aon charactar a-rithist ’s a-rithist.

column1: Try to avoid repeating the same type of character: you need to mix up letters, numbers and punctuation.
column3: Feuch is seachain an aon seòrsa de charactar a-rithist ’s a-rithist: feumaidh tu measgachadh de litrichean, àireamhan is puingeachadh.

column1: Try to avoid sequences like 1234 or abcd.
column3: Feuch is seachain sreathan mar 1234 no abcd.

column1: Password needs to be longer. Try to add more letters, numbers and punctuation.
column3: Feumaidh faclan-faire a bhith nas fhaide. Feuch is cuir ris barrachd litrichean, àireamhan is puingeachadh.

column1: Mix uppercase and lowercase and try to use a number or two.
column3: Cleachd litrichean mòra ’s beaga agus feuch an cleachd thu àireamh no dhà.

column1: Adding more letters, numbers and punctuation will make the password stronger.
column3: Bidh e nas treasa ma chuireas tu barrachd litrichean, àireamhan is puingeachadh ris.

column1: The new password is too short
column3: Tha am facal-faire ùr ro ghoirid

column1: The new password is too simple
column3: Tha am facal-faire ùr ro shimplidh

column3: Tha an seann fhacal-faire agus am fear ùr ro choltach ri chèile

column3: Chaidh am facal-faire ùr a chleachdadh o chionn ghoirid mu thràth.

column1: The old and new passwords are the same
column3: Tha an seann fhacal-faire ’s am fear ùra co-ionnann

column3: Chaidh am facal-faire agad atharrachadh on a rinn thu dearbhadh an toiseach!

column3: Tha sinn duilich ach chan eil an t-ainm-cleachdaiche seo ri fhaighinn. Feuch fear eile.

column1: To edit a shortcut, choose the “Send Keystroke” action, press the keyboard shortcut button and hold down the new keys or press Backspace to clear.
column3: Gus ath-ghoirid a dheasachadh, tagh an gnìomh “Cuir buille-iuchrach”, brùth putan ath-ghoirid meur-chlàir is cum sìos na h-iuchraichean ùra no brùth Backspace gus fhalamhachadh.

column1: Please tap the target markers as they appear on screen to calibrate the tablet.

Mhothaich sinn do bhriogadh claon, ag ath-thòiseachadh…
Seall a’ chobhair air an sgrìn

column1: Default location for the Create/Restore disk image dialogs
column3: Ionad bunaiteach nan còmhraidhean airson cruthachadh/aiseag ìomhaighean diosga

column1: Default location for the Create/Restore disk image dialogs. If blank the ~/Documents folder is used.

column1: Disks provides an easy way to inspect, format, partition, and configure disks and block devices.
column3: Bheir Diosgan dòigh furasta dhut gus diosgan is uidheaman bloca a sgrùdadh, fhòrmatadh, a phàirteachadh ’s a rèiteachadh.

column1: Using Disks, you can view SMART data, manage devices, benchmark physical disks, and image USB sticks.
column3: Le Diosgan, ’s urrainn dhut dàta SMART a shealltainn, uidheaman a stiùireadh, tomhas-measaidh air diosgan fiosaigeach a dhèanamh is ìomhaighean de USB sticks a chruthachadh.

column3: Stiùirich na diosgan agad gun duilgheadas
Tagh na h-ìomhaigh(ean) diosga ri am munntachadh

column1: If checked, the mount will be read-only. This is useful if you don’t want the underlying disk image to be modified
column3: Ma chuireas tu cromag ris, bidh am munntachadh ri leughadh a-mhàin. Tha seo feumail mur eil thu ag iarraidh gun dèid ìomhaigh an diosga air a bheil e stèidhichte atharrachadh.
Mearachd a’ ceangal ri udisks daemon: %s (%s, %d)

column3: Ceangail ris agus munntaich co-dhiù aon fhaidhle ìomhaigh diosga.

column3: Cha ghabh “%s” fhosgladh – saoil nach deach an draibh a mhunntachadh?
Mearachd a’ ceangal ìomhaigh an diosga ris: %s (%s, %d)
A bheil thu airson stad a chur air na h-obraichean?

column1: Closing now stops the running jobs and leads to a corrupt result.

column1: Frequency of errors while reading raw data from the disk. A non-zero value indicates a problem with either the disk surface or read/write heads

Co mheud cuairt tòiseachaidh/stadaidh a tha aig an fheàrsaid

column1: Count of remapped sectors. When the hard drive finds a read/write/verification error, it marks the sector as “reallocated” and transfers data to a special reserved area (spare area)

column3: Am marghan aig seanail rè leughaidh an dàta.
Tricead nam mearachdan rè gnìomhan suidheachaidh

column3: Èifeachdas cuibheasach nan obrachaidhean rè gnìomhan suidheachaidh

column1: Number of remapping operations. The raw value of this attribute shows the total number of (successful and unsuccessful) attempts to transfer data from reallocated sectors to a spare area
column3: Co mheud turas a chaidh ath-mhapachadh a dhèanamh. Seallaidh luach amh na buaidhe seo co mheud turas gu h-iomlan (soirbheachail is neo-shoirbheachail) a dh’fheuchadh ri dàta a ghluasad o roinn ath-riarachadh gu raon falamh.
Àireamh nan earrannan a tha ri an dèiligeadh

column1: Number of sectors waiting to be remapped. If the sector waiting to be remapped is subsequently written or read successfully, this value is decreased and the sector is not remapped. Read errors on the sector will not remap the sector, it will only be remapped on a failed write attempt
column3: Àireamh nan earrannan a tha a’ fuireach ri ath-mhapachadh. Ma thèid an earrann a tha ri mhapachadh a sgrìobhadh no a leughadh gu soirbheachail às a dhèidh sin, thèid an luach seo a lùghdachadh agus cha dèid an earrann ath-mhapachadh. Cha dèanar ath-mhapachadh air an earrann ri linn mearachd leughaidh, cha dèid ath-mhapachadh ach an dèidh oidhirp sgrìobhaidh a dh’fhàillig.
Cunntas nan earrannan nach gabh a cheartachadh

column1: The total number of uncorrectable errors when reading/writing a sector. A rise in the value of this attribute indicates defects of the disk surface and/or problems in the mechanical subsystem
column3: Àireamh iomlan nam mearachdan nach gabh a cheartachadh nuair a leughar/sgrìobhar earrann. Ma thèid an luach seo an àirde, tha seo a’ comharradh gu bheil rudeigin cearr air uachdar an diosga agus/no gu bheil duilgheadas san fho-shiostam mheacanaigeach

column1: Number of CRC errors during UDMA mode

column1: Number of errors while writing to disk (or) multi-zone error rate (or) flying-height

column1: WARNING: The Secure Erase command may take a very long time to complete, can’t be canceled and may not work properly with some hardware. column1: Benchmarking involves measuring the transfer rate on various area of the device as well as measuring how long it takes to seek from one random area to another. Please back up important data before using the write benchmark.
column3: Ma nì thu tomhas-measaidh, thèid astar nan tar-chur air diofar raointean an uidheam a thomhas agus dè cho fada ’s a bheir e ’s e a’ dol o àite air thuaiream gu àite eile air thuaiream. B’ fheairrde dhut lethbhreac-glèidhidh a dhèanamh de dhàta cudromach sam bith mus fheuch thu ri tomhas-measaidh an sgrìobhaidh.

column1: Benchmarking the write-rate of a disk requires exclusive access to the disk (e.g. the disk or its partitions cannot be mounted or in use) and involves reading data and then writing it back. As a result, the contents of the disk is not changed.\n\nIf not checked, the write-part of the benchmark will not be done but on the other hand exclusive access to the device is not needed (e.g. the disk or device can be in use).
column3: Ma tha thu airson tomhas-measaidh a dhèanamh air reat sgrìobhaidh diosga, bidh feum air inntrigeadh às-dùnach dhan diosga (tha sin a’ ciallachadh nach fhaod an diosga no gin dhe na pàirteachaidhean aige a bhith ’gan cleachdadh no air am munntachadh) agus bithear a’ leughadh dàta uaithe ’s ’ga sgrìobhaidh air ais ann. Ri linn sin, chan atharraich na tha air an diosga.\n\nMur an cuir thu cromag ris, cha dèanar tomhas air an sgrìobhadh san tomhas-mheasaidh agus cha bhi feum air inntrigeadh às-dùnach dhan diosga (tha sin a’ ciallachadh gum faod an diosga no an t-uidheam a bhith ’ga chleachdadh).

column1: Number of samples. Bigger number produces a more accurate picture of access time patterns but takes more time.
column3: Co mheud sampall. Gheibh thu beachd nas fhearr air pàtranan nan amannan inntrigidh ma chleachdas tu barrachd shampall ach bheir e nas fhaide.

column1: The number of MiB (1048576 bytes) to read/write for each sample. Big sample sizes tend to produce more accurate benchmarks at the cost of the benchmark taking more time.
column3: Co mheud MiB (1048576 bytes) a thèid a leughadh/sgrìobhadh airson gach sampaill. Gheibh thu tomhas-measaidh nas fhearr ma chleachdas tu sampall mòr ach bheir an tomhas-measaidh nas fhaide.

column1: Number of samples. Bigger number produces more smooth graphs but the benchmark will take more time.
column3: Co mheud sampall. Gheibh thu graf nas rèidhe le barrachd dhiubh ach bheil e nas fhaide.

column1: This is equivalent to Master Boot Record bootable flag. It is normally only used for GPT partitions on MBR systems

column1: Indicates that EFI firmware should ignore the content of the partition and not try to read from it

column1: The size of the image to create

Resizing a filesystem can lead to data loss. You are advised to backup your data before. The resize operation will take longer if a lot of data has to be moved. The minimal size is calculated according to the current content. Keep additional free space for the filesystem to work fast and reliably.
column3: Nuair a dh’atharraicheas tu meud an t-siostaim-fhaichlichean, dh’fhaoidte gun dèid dàta air chall. Mholamaid gun dèan thu lethbhreac-glèidhidh dhen dàta roimhe sin. Bheir obrachadh an ath-mheudachaidh nas fhaide ma bhios torr dàta feumach air gluasad. Thèid am meud as ìsle àireamhachadh a-rèir na susbainte làithrich. Cum àite saor a bharrachd ach am bi an siotam-fhaidhlichean luath is seasmhach.

column1: Value identifies whether to repeat or randomize playback through the collection. Allowed values are: “none” (repeat and shuffle are off), “song” (repeat current song), “all” (repeat playlist, no shuffle), “shuffle” (shuffle playlist, presumes repeat all).
column3: Innsidh an luach am bu chòir ath-chluich no nithean sa chruinneachadh a chluich air thuaiream. Seo na luachan ceadaichte: “none” (tha ath-chluich is cluich air thuaiream dheth), “song” (ath-chluich an t-òran làithreach), “all” (ath-chluich an liosta-chluich gun a bhith ’ga cluich air thuaiream), “shuffle” (cluich na h-òrain air an liosta-chluich air thuaiream, an dùil gun dèid na h-uile òran ath-chluich).

column1: Network Tools is a utility to perform advanced networking analysis operations. It features a range of networking tools that are typically done on the command line, but allows you to perform them with a graphical interface.
column3: ’S e goireas a th’ anns na h-innealan lìonraidh gus anailis adhartach a dhèanamh air an lìonra. Tha iomadh inneal lìonraidh ’na bhroinn a chleachdar air an loidhne-àithne mar a trice, ach leigidh e leat cuideachd an cleachdadh le eadar-aghaidh ghrafaigeach.

column1: With Network Tools, you can perform the following: ping, netstat, traceroute, port scans, lookup, finger and whois.
column3: Seo na nì thu leis na h-innealan lìonraidh: ping, netstat, traceroute, sganadh puirt, lookup, finger agus whois.
Seall am fiosrachadh mun lìonra agad

column1: A simple application to access, organize and share your photos on GNOME. It is meant to be a simple and elegant replacement for using a file manager to deal with photos. Seamless cloud integration is offered through GNOME Online Accounts.
column3: Seo aplacaid simplidh gus na dealbhan agad inntrigeadh, a chur an rian ’s a cho-roinneadh air GNOME. Tha fainear dhuinn gur e roghainn simplidh is snasail a th’ innte an àite manaidsear nam faidhlichean gus dèiligeadh ri dealbhan. Gheibh thu filleadh a-steach air neul le cunntasan air loidhne GNOME.

column1: Take a Screenshot of the Current Window

GNOME Screenshot is a simple utility that lets you take pictures of your computer screen. Screenshots can be of your whole screen, any specific application, or a selected rectangular area. You can also copy the captured screenshot directly into the GNOME clipboard and paste it into other applications.
column3: ’S e goireas simplidh a th’ ann an glacadh-sgrìn GNOME a leigeas leat dealbhan a thogail de sgrìn a’ choimpiutair agad. Togaidh tu glacadh-sgrìn dhen sgrìn air fad, de dh’aplacaid shònraichte no de raon ceart-cheàrnach a thagh thu. ’S urrainn dhut lethbhreac dhen ghlacadh-sgrìn a chur ann an stòr-bhòrd GNOME sa bhad ’s a chur ann an aplacaidean eile.

column1: GNOME Screenshot allows you to take screenshots even when it’s not open: just press the PrtSc button on your keyboard, and a snapshot of your whole screen will be saved to your Pictures folder. Hold Alt while pressing PrtSc and you will get a screenshot of only the currently selected window.
column3: Leigidh glacadh-sgrìn GNOME leat glacaidhean-sgrìn a thogail fiù mur eil e fosgailte: cha leig thu leas ach brùthadh air a’ phutan PrtSc air a’ mheur-chlàr agad agus thèid glacadh dhen sgrìn air fad agad a chur ann am pasgan nan Dealbhan agad. Cum sìos Alt fhad ’s a tha thu a’ brùthadh PrtSc gus nach faigh thu glacadh ach dhen uinneag air a thaghadh aig an àm.

column1:
%s [OPTION…] COMMAND

Execute COMMAND while inhibiting some session functionality.

  -h, --help        Show this help
  --version         Show program version
  --app-id ID       The application id to use
                    when inhibiting (optional)
  --reason REASON   The reason for inhibiting (optional)
  --inhibit ARG     Things to inhibit, colon-separated list of:
                    logout, switch-user, suspend, idle, automount
  --inhibit-only    Do not launch COMMAND and wait forever instead

If no --inhibit option is specified, idle is assumed.
column3:
%s [ROGHAINN…] ÀITHNE

Ruith ÀITHNE fhad ’s a thèid cuid a dh’fhoincseanan seisein a bhacadh.

  -h, --help        Seall a’ chobhair seo
  --version         Seall an tionndadh dhen phrògram
  --app-id ID       ID ana h-aplacaid a thèid a chleachdadh
                    leis a’ bhacadh (roghainneil)
  --reason ADHBHAR  Adhbhar a’ bhacaidh (rogainneil)
  --inhibit ARG     Nithean ri am bacadh, liosta air a sgaradh le
                    còileanan de:
                    logout, switch-user, suspend, idle, automount
  --inhibit-only    Na cuir an ÀITHNE gu dol is dèan feitheamh gun chrìch
                    ’na àite

Mura deach an roghainn --inhibit a shònrachadh, thathar an dùil
air idle.
A’ leigeil seachad gach bacadair a tha ann
Na faighnich airson dearbhadh a’ chleachdaiche

column1: GNOME Shell extensions have a UUID property; this key lists extensions which should be loaded. Any extension that wants to be loaded needs to be in this list. You can also manipulate this list with the EnableExtension and DisableExtension D-Bus methods on org.gnome.Shell.
column3: Tha buadh UUID aig leudachain Slige GNOME; seallaidh an iuchair sin na leudachain a bu chòir luchdadh. Feumaidh gach leudachan a tha ag iarraidh luchdadh a bhith air an liosta seo. ’S urrainn dhut an liosta seo atharrachadh cuideachd leis na modhan D-Bus EnableExtension agus DisableExtension air org.gnome.Shell.

column1: Disable all extensions the user has enabled without affecting the “enabled-extension” setting.

column1: GNOME Shell will only load extensions that claim to support the current running version. Enabling this option will disable this check and try to load all extensions regardless of the versions they claim to support.
column3: Cha luchdaich Slige GNOME ach leudachain a dh’innseas gu bheil iad co-chòrdail leis an tionndadh a tha ’ga ruith. Ma chuireas tu an roghainn seo an comas, thèid an dearbhadh a chur à comas agus feuchaidh sinn ris a h-uile leudachan a luchdadh ge b’ e dè na tionndaidhean ris an cuir iad taic dhan rèir-san.

column3: A bheil thu airson crìoch a chur air %d pròiseas a thagh thu?

column3: A bheil thu airson stad a chur air a’ phròiseas a thagh thu?

column1: Killing a process may destroy data, break the session or introduce a security risk. Only unresponsive processes should be killed.
column3: Ma mharbhas tu dàta, dh’fhaoidte gun sgrios thu dàta, gum bris thu an seisean no gun adhbharaich thu cunnart tèarainteachd. Cha bu chòir dhut a mharbhadh ach pròiseasan nach eil a’ freagairt tuilleadh.

column1: Ending a process may destroy data, break the session or introduce a security risk. Only unresponsive processes should be ended.
column3: Ma chrìochnaicheas tu dàta, dh’fhaoidte gun sgrios thu dàta, gum bris thu an seisean no gun adhbharaich thu cunnart tèarainteachd. Cha bu chòir dhut a chrìochnachadh ach pròiseasan nach eil a’ freagairt tuilleadh.

column1: Stopping a process may destroy data, break the session or introduce a security risk. Only unresponsive processes should be stopped.
column3: Ma chuireas tu stad air pròiseas, dh’fhaoidte gun sgrios thu dàta, gum bris thu an seisean no gun adhbharaich thu cunnart tèarainteachd. Cha bu chòir dhut stad a chur ach air pròiseasan nach eil a’ freagairt tuilleadh.

column1: Change Priority of the selected process
column3: Atharraich prìomhachas a’ phròiseis a thagh thu

column1: Change Priority of the selected process
column3: Atharraich prìomhachas an %d phròiseis a thagh thu

column1: Change Priority of the selected process
column3: Atharraich am prìomhachas aig %d phròiseasan a thagh thu

column1: Change Priority of the selected process
column3: Atharraich am prìomhachas aig %d phròiseasan a thagh thu

column1: The priority of a process is given by its nice value. A lower nice value corresponds to a higher priority.
column3: Tha an nice value aig pròiseas a’ suidheachadh a’ phrìomhachais aige. Bheir luach nas lugha prìomhachas nas àirde.

column1: GNOME Terminal is a terminal emulator application for accessing a UNIX shell environment which can be used to run programs available on your system.
column3: ’S e aplacaid aithrisiche tèirmineil a th’ ann an Tèirmineal GNOME gus àrainneachd slige UNIX inntrigeadh a ghabhas cleachdadh gus prògraman a ruith a tha ri am faighinn air an t-siostam agad.

column1: It supports several profiles, multiple tabs and implements several keyboard shortcuts.
column3: Cuiridh e taic ri iomadh pròifil, taba ’s ath-ghoiridean meur-chlàir.

column1: Open Terminal is a plugin for the Files application that adds a menu item to the context menu to open a terminal in the currently browsed directory.
column3: ’S e plugan a th’ ann am “Fosgail tèirmineal” airson aplacaid nam faidhlichean a chuireas nì ris a’ chlàr-taice cho-theacsail gus tèirmineal fhosgladh sa phasgan a thagh thu.

column1: “%s” is not a valid application ID
FD passing of stdin is not supported
column3: Cha chuirear taic ri cur an FD o stdin

column1: FD passing of stdout is not supported
column3: Cha chuirear taic ri cur an FD o stdout

column1: FD passing of stderr is not supported
column3: Cha chuirear taic ri cur an FD o stderr
Cha ghabh FD %d a chur dà thuras
Sìn air adhart tuairisgeulaiche an fhaidhle
Cuir an uinneag sa mhodh làn-sgrìn

column1: Set the window size; for example: 80x24, or 80x24+200+200 (COLSxROWS+X+Y)
column3: Suidhich meud na h-uinneige; mar eisimpleir: 80x24 no 80x24+200+200 (COLBHANxRÀGHAN+X+Y)
Chan fhaod thu an roghainn %s a chleachdadh ach aon turas

column1: “%s” is not a valid zoom factor
Zoom value “%s” is outside allowed range
column3: Tha luach “%s” an t-sùmaidh taobh a-muigh an rainse dlighich

column1: Use the given profile instead of the default profile
column3: Cleachd a’ phròifil a chaidh a thoirt seachad seach an tè thùsail

column1: Set the terminal’s zoom factor (1.0 = normal size)
column3: Suidhich factar an t-sùmaidh airson an tèirmineil (1.0 = meud àbhaisteach)
Fuirich gus am fàg a’ chlann

column1: “%s” needs the command to run as arguments after “--”
column3: Iarraidh “%s” gun dèid an àithne a ruith ’na argamaidean às dèidh “--”
Ainm a’ phròifil a leughas duine
Ainm a’ phròifil a tha furasta leughadh do dhuine.

column1: Default color of text in the terminal
column3: Dath tùsail aig teacsa an tèirmineil

column1: Default color of text in the terminal, as a color specification (can be HTML-style hex digits, or a color name such as “red”).
column3: Dath tùsail aig teacsa an tèirmineil ’na shònrachadh datha (faodaidh seo a bhith ’nan àireamhan sia-dheicheach ann an stoidhle HTML no ainm datha, can “red”).
Dath tùsail aig cùlaibh an tèirmineil

column1: Default color of terminal background, as a color specification (can be HTML-style hex digits, or a color name such as “red”).
column3: Dath tùsail aig cùlaibh an tèirmineil ’na shònrachadh datha (faodaidh seo a bhith ’nan àireamhan sia-dheicheach ann an stoidhle HTML no ainm datha, can “red”).

column1: Default color of bold text in the terminal
column3: Dath tùsail aig teacsa trom an tèirmineil

column1: Default color of bold text in the terminal, as a color specification (can be HTML-style hex digits, or a color name such as “red”). This is ignored if bold-color-same-as-fg is true.
column3: Dath tùsail aig teacsa an tèirmineil ’na shònrachadh datha (faodaidh seo a bhith ’nan àireamhan sia-dheicheach ann an stoidhle HTML no ainm datha, can “red”). Thèid seo a leigeil seachad mas e “true” a th’ ann am bold-color-same-as-fg.

column1: Whether bold text should use the same color as normal text
column3: Co-dhiù am bi an aon dath air teacsa trom ’s a tha air teacsa àbhaisteach gus nach bi

column1: If true, boldface text will be rendered using the same color as normal text.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, thèid teacsa trom a reandaradh leis an aon dath ’s a thèid teacsa àbhaisteach.

column1: Whether to use custom cursor colors
column3: Co-dhiù an cleachd an cùrsair dathan gnàthaichte gus nach cleachd

column1: If true, use the cursor colors from the profile.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, cleachd dàthan a’ chùrsair on phròifil.

column1: Custom color of the background of the terminal’s cursor, as a color specification (can be HTML-style hex digits, or a color name such as “red”). This is ignored if cursor-colors-set is false.
column3: Dath gnàthaichte aig cùlaibh cùrsair an tèirmineil ’na shònrachadh datha (faodaidh seo a bhith ’nan àireamhan sia-dheicheach ann an stoidhle HTML no ainm datha, can “red”). Thèid seo a leigeil seachad mas e “false” a th’ ann am cursor-colors-set.

column1: Custom color for the foreground of the text character at the terminal’s cursor position, as a color specification (can be HTML-style hex digits, or a color name such as “red”). This is ignored if cursor-colors-set is false.
column3: Dath gnàthaichte aig beulaibh a’ charactar teacsa air ionad cùrsair an tèirmineil ’na shònrachadh datha (faodaidh seo a bhith ’nan àireamhan sia-dheicheach ann an stoidhle HTML no ainm datha, can “red”). Thèid seo a leigeil seachad mas e “false” a th’ ann am cursor-colors-set.

column1: Whether to use custom highlight colors
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid dathan soillseachaidh gnàthaichte a chleachdadh gus nach dèid

column1: If true, use the highlight colors from the profile.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, cleachd na dàthan soillseachaidh on phròifil.

column1: Custom color of the background of the terminal’s highlight, as a color specification (can be HTML-style hex digits, or a color name such as “red”). This is ignored if highlight-colors-set is false.
column3: Dath gnàthaichte aig cùlaibh soillseachaidh an tèirmineil ’na shònrachadh datha (faodaidh seo a bhith ’nan àireamhan sia-dheicheach ann an stoidhle HTML no ainm datha, can “red”). Thèid seo a leigeil seachad mas e “false” a th’ ann am highlight-colors-set.

column1: Custom color for the foreground of the text character at the terminal’s highlight position, as a color specification (can be HTML-style hex digits, or a color name such as “red”). This is ignored if highlight-colors-set is false.
column3: Dath gnàthaichte aig beulaibh a’ charactar teacsa air ionad soillseachaidh an tèirmineil ’na shònrachadh datha (faodaidh seo a bhith ’nan àireamhan sia-dheicheach ann an stoidhle HTML no ainm datha, can “red”). Thèid seo a leigeil seachad mas e “false” a th’ ann am highlight-colors-set.
Co-dhiù a bheil teacsa trom ceadaichte gus nach eil

column1: If true, allow applications in the terminal to make text boldface.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, faodaidh aplacaidean teacsa trom a nochdadh san tèirmineal.

column1: Whether to ring the terminal bell
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid clag an tèirmineil a sheinn

column1: List of ASCII punctuation characters that are not to be treated as part of a word when doing word-wise selection
column3: Liosta de charactaran puingeachaidh ASCII nach dèid dèiligeadh riutha mar phàirt de dh’fhacal nuair a thèid taghadh facal air an fhacal

column1: Whether to show menubar in new windows/tabs
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid am bàr clàr-taice a shealltainn le uinneagan/tabaichean ùra

column1: True if the menubar should be shown in new window
column3: Suidhich seo air “true” ma tha thu airson am bàr clàr-taice a shealltainn ann an uinneag ùr

column1: Number of columns in newly created terminal windows. Has no effect if use_custom_default_size is not enabled.
column3: An àireamh de cholbhan a bhios aig uinneagan tèirmineil air an ùr-chruthachadh. Cha dèan seo dad ach ma bhios use_custom_default_size an comas.

column1: Number of rows in newly created terminal windows. Has no effect if use_custom_default_size is not enabled.
column3: An àireamh de ràghan a bhios aig uinneagan tèirmineil air an ùr-chruthachadh. Cha dèan seo dad ach ma bhios use_custom_default_size an comas.
Co-dhiù an dèid am bàr-sgolaidh a shealltainn

column1: Number of lines to keep in scrollback
column3: An àireamh de loidhnichean san sgroladh air ais

column1: Number of scrollback lines to keep around. You can scroll back in the terminal by this number of lines; lines that don’t fit in the scrollback are discarded. If scrollback_unlimited is true, this value is ignored.
column3: An àireamh de loidhnichean a thèid a chumail gus sgroladh air ais. Seo an àireamh de loidhnichean as urrainn dhut sgoladh air ais san tèirmineil ’s thèid an còrr a thilgeil air falbh. Thèid an luach seo a chur dhan dàrna taobh ma tha scrollback_unlimited suidhichte air “true”.

column1: Whether an unlimited number of lines should be kept in scrollback
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid loidhnichean gun chrìch a chumail san sgoladh air ais gus nach dèid

column1: If true, scrollback lines will never be discarded. The scrollback history is stored on disk temporarily, so this may cause the system to run out of disk space if there is a lot of output to the terminal.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, cha dèid loidhnichean sgrolaidh air ais a thilgeil air falbh idir. thèid eachdraidh an sgrolaidh air ais a ghlèidheadh air a diosga ’s le sin dh’fhaoidte gun ruith an rum air an diosga ort ma tha torr às-chur san tèirmineal.

column1: Whether to scroll to the bottom when a key is pressed
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid sgroladh gun bhonn le brùthadh air iuchair gus nach dèid

column1: If true, pressing a key jumps the scrollbar to the bottom.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, leumaidh am bàr-sgrolaidh gun bhonn le brùthadh air iuchair.

column1: Whether to scroll to the bottom when there’s new output
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid sgroladh gun bhonn nuair a bhios às-chur ùr ann gus nach dèid

column1: If true, whenever there’s new output the terminal will scroll to the bottom.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, nì an tèirmineil sgroladh gun bhonn nuair a bhios às-chur ùr ann.

column1: What to do with the terminal when the child command exits
column3: Dè thèid a dhèanamh leis an tèirmineil nuair a dh’fhàgas an àithne-cloinne

column1: Possible values are “close” to close the terminal, “restart” to restart the command, and “hold” to keep the terminal open with no command running inside.
column3: Faodaidh tu seo a shuidheachadh air “close” gus an tèirmineal a dhùnadh no air “restart” gus an àithne a thòiseachadh às ùr is air “hold” gus an tèirmineal a chumail fosgailte gun àithne ’ga ruith ann.

column1: Whether to launch the command in the terminal as a login shell
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid an àithne san tèirmineal a thòiseachadh ’na slige clàraidh a-steach gus nach dèid

column1: If true, the command inside the terminal will be launched as a login shell (argv[0] will have a hyphen in front of it).
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, thèid an àithne san tèirmineal a thòiseachadh ’na slige clàraidh a-steach (bidh tàthan ro argv[0]).

column1: Whether to run a custom command instead of the shell
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid àithne ghnàthaichte a ruith an àite na slige gus nach dèid

column1: If true, the value of the custom_command setting will be used in place of running a shell.
column3: Mas e “true” a th’ ann, thèid an luach air an roghainn custom_command a chleachdadh an àite slige a ruith.
Co-dhiù an dèan an cùrsair priobadh gus nach dèan

column1: The possible values are “system” to use the global cursor blinking settings, or “on” or “off” to set the mode explicitly.
column3: ’S urrainn dhut “system” a chleachdadh airson roghainnean coitcheann a thaobh priobadh a’ chùrsair no “on” no “off” gus am modh a shuidheachadh gu sònraichte.

column1: Custom command to use instead of the shell
column3: Àithne ghnàthaichte an àite na slige

column1: Run this command in place of the shell, if use_custom_command is true.
column3: Ruith an àithne seo an àite na slige mas e “true” a th’ ann an use_custom_command.

column1: A Pango font name and size
The code sequence the Backspace key generates
column3: An sreath de chòdaichean a ghineas an iuchair Backspace

column1: The code sequence the Delete key generates
column3: An sreath de chòdaichean a ghineas an iuchair Delete

column1: Whether to use the colors from the theme for the terminal widget
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid na dathan aig an ùrlar a chleachdadh airson widget an tèirmineil gus nach dèid

column1: Whether to use the system monospace font
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid cruth-clò aon-leud an t-siostaim a chleachdadh no nach dèid

column1: Whether to rewrap the terminal contents on window resize
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid susbaint an tèirmineil a phasgadh às ùr le ath-mheudachadh na h-uinneige gus nach dèid

column3: Co-dhiù am bi caractaran le leud ioma-fhillte caol no leathan gus nach bi nuair a bhios còdachadh UTF-8 ’ga chleachdadh

column3: Ath-ghoirid a’ mheur-chlàir gus taba ùr a dhùnadh

column3: Ath-ghoirid a’ mheur-chlàir gus an taba làithreach a ghluasad gu clì

column3: Ath-ghoirid a’ mheur-chlàir gus an taba làithreach a ghluasad gu deas

Ath-ghoirid a’ mheur-chlàir gus a’ chobhair a thòiseachadh

column3: Ath-ghoirid a’ mheur-chlàir gus an cruth-clò a dhèanamh nas motha

column3: Ath-ghoirid a’ mheur-chlàir gus am meud tùsail a chur air a’ chruth-chlò

column1: Whether the menubar has access keys
column3: Co-dhiù am bi iuchraichean inntrigidh aig a’ bhàr clàir-thaice gus nach bi

column1: Whether to have Alt+letter access keys for the menubar. They may interfere with some applications run inside the terminal so it’s possible to turn them off.
column3: Co-dhiù am bi iuchraichean inntrigidh Alt+litir aig a’ bhàr clàir-thaice gus nach bi. Dh’fhaoidte gum buin iad ri cuid a dh’aplacaidean a tha ’gan ruith san tèirmineal, mar sin faodaidh tu an cur dheth.
Co-dhiù a bheil ath-ghoiridean an comas gus nach eil

column1: Whether shortcuts are enabled. They may interfere with some applications run inside the terminal so it’s possible to turn them off.
column3: Co-dhiù a bheil ath-ghoiridean an comas gus nach eil. Dh’fhaoidte gum buin iad ri cuid a dh’aplacaidean a tha ’gan ruith san tèirmineal, mar sin faodaidh tu an cur dheth.

column1: Whether the standard GTK shortcut for menubar access is enabled
column3: Co-dhiù a bheil an ath-ghoirid thùsail aig GTK an comas gus am bàr clàir-taice inntrigeadh gus nach eil

column1: Normally you can access the menubar with F10. This can also be customized via gtkrc (gtk-menu-bar-accel = \"whatever\"). This option allows the standard menubar accelerator to be disabled.
column3: ’S urrainn dhut am bàr clàir-taice inntrigeadh le F10 o thùs. ’S urrainn dhut seo a ghnàthachadh slighe gtkrc (gtk-menu-bar-accel = \"rudeigin\"). Leigidh an roghainn seo leat ath-ghoirid thùsail a’ bhàir clàir-thaice a chur à comas.

column1: Whether the shell integration is enabled
column3: Co-dhiù a bheil filleadh a-steach na slige an comas gus nach eil
Liosta dhe na còdachaidhean a tha ri làimh

column1: A subset of possible encodings are presented in the Encoding submenu. This is a list of encodings to appear there.
column3: Thèid fo-sheata dhe na còdachaidhean a ghabhas cleachdadh a shealltainn ann am fo-chlàr-taice a’ chòdachaidh. Seo liosta dhe na còdachaidhean a nochdas ann.

column1: Whether to ask for confirmation before closing a terminal
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid dearbhadh iarraidh mus dèid tèirmineal a dhùnadh gus nach dèid

column1: Whether to show the menubar in new windows
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid am bàr clàr-taice a shealltainn le uinneagan ùra gus nach dèid

column1: Whether to open new terminals as windows or tabs
column3: Co-dhiù an dèid tèirmineal ùr fhosgladh ’na uinneag no taba gus nach dèid

column1: When to show the tabs bar
column3: Cuin a thèid bàr nan tabaichean a shealltainn

column1: The position of the tab bar
column3: An t-ionad aig bàr nan tabaichean
An eugsamhail dhen ùrlar a thèid a chleachdadh

column1: Show _menubar by default in new terminals
column3: Seall am :bàr clàr-taice a ghnàth ann an tèirmineil ùr

column1: _Enable mnemonics (such as Alt+F to open the File menu)
column3: Cuir ath-ghoiridean cuimhneachaidh an c_omas (mar Alt+F gus an clàr-taice “Faidhle” fhosgladh)

column1: Enable the _menu accelerator key (F10 by default)
column3: Cuir ath-ghoirid a’ chlàir-_taice an comas (F10 a ghnàth)

column1: _Profile used when launching a new terminal:

column1: It also optionally integrates with the GNOME Shell, allowing you see the current conditions of the most recently searched cities by just typing its name in the Activities Overview.
column3: Gabhaidh amalachadh leis an t-slige GNOME ma thogras tu ’s mar sin airson nam bailtean a lorg thu o chionn goirid, cha leig thu leas ach ainm baile a sgrìobhadh ann am foir-shealladh nan gnìomhachdan ach am faic thu an aimsir airson a’ bhaile ud.

column1: Nautilus, also known as Files, is the default file manager of the GNOME desktop. It provides a simple and integrated way of managing your files and browsing your file system.
column3: ’S e am manaidsear fhaidhlichean tùsail aig an deasga GNOME a th’ anns an Nautilus ris a chanar Faidhlichean cuideachd. Bheir e dòigh simplidh ’s amalaichte dhut gus na faidhlichean agad a stiùireadh ’s an siostam-fhaidhlichean a rùrachadh.

column1: Nautilus supports all the basic functions of a file manager and more. It can search and manage your files and folders, both locally and on a network, read and write data to and from removable media, run scripts, and launch applications. It has three views: Icon Grid, Icon List, and Tree List. Its functions can be extended with plugins and scripts.
column3: Bheir Nautilus taic do na h-uile foincsean bunasach aig manaidsear fhaidhlichean ’s a bharrachd. Tha e comasach air lorg sna faidhlichean agus pasganan agad ’s an stiùireadh, an dà chuid gu ionadail ’s air lìonra, air dàta a leughadh ’s a sgrìobhadh gu uidheaman so-ghiùlain, air sgriobtaichean a ruith agus air prògraman a thòiseachadh. Tha trì seallaidhean ri fhaighinn: griod de dh’ìomhaigheagan, liosta no craobh. Gabhaidh na feartan a leudachadh le plugain ’s sgriobtaichean.

column1: Where to position newly open tabs in browser windows
column3: Càit an dèid tabaichean a tha air ùr-fhosgladh a chur ann an uinneagan brabhsair

column1: If set to “after-current-tab”, then new tabs are inserted after the current tab. If set to “end”, then new tabs are appended to the end of the tab list.
column3: Ma thaghas tu “after-current-tab”, nochdaidh tabaichean ùra an dèidh an taba làithrich. Ma thaghas tu “end”, nochdaidh tabaichean ùra aig deireadh liosta nan tabaichean.

column1: Always use the location entry, instead of the pathbar
column3: Cleachd ion-chur an ionaid an-còmhnaidh, na cleachd bàr na slighe

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus browser windows will always use a textual input entry for the location toolbar, instead of the pathbar.
column3: Ma thaghas tu “true” air a shon, seallaidh uinneagan brabhsair Nautilus innteart teacsa airson bàr-inneal an ionaid seach bàr na slighe.
Co-dhiù an dèid lorg ath-chùrsach a dhèanamh gus nach dèid

column1: In which locations Nautilus should search on subfolders. Available values are “local-only”, “always”, “never”.
column3: Na h-ionadan sam bu chòir dha Nautilus lorg sna fo-phasganan. Seo na luachan a tha ri fhaighinn: “local-only”, “always”, “never”.
